A new R1.2 bn fresh produce market in Mbombela, Mpumalanga, has been earmarked to drag the province out of economic recession. It's economy contracted by 6 percent last quarter, prompting calls for an emergency investment. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 MBOMBELA - A new R1.2 billiion fresh produce market in Mbombela, Mpumalanga, has been earmarked to drag the province out of economic recession. Its economy contracted by 6 percent last quarter, prompting calls for an emergency investment. READ: Mpumalanga Premier reshuffles cabinet Premier Refilwe Mtsweni-Tsipane, in her State of the Province Address, called on farmers to help revive the economy. She is hoping this new market will facilitate that. Watch the video above for more on this story